sequenceDiagram
    actor Customer
    actor Admin
    actor Therapist
    participant System as Web Portal
    participant DB as Booking Database
    participant Mail as Email Service

    %% Customer Authentication and Browsing
    Customer->>System: Login / Authenticate
    System-->>Customer: Show Dashboard
    
    Customer->>System: Browse Therapists & Services
    System->>DB: Fetch Available Services
    DB-->>System: Return DB Records
    System-->>Customer: Display Options
    
    %% Booking Creation
    Customer->>System: Details + Pay Token Amount
    System->>DB: Create Booking Entry (Status: Pending)
    DB-->>System: Booking Created Successfully
    System-->>Customer: Booking Confirmation (Pending Admin Approval)

    %% Admin Review & Approval
    Admin->>System: Login & View Appointment Requests
    System->>DB: Fetch Pending Bookings
    DB-->>System: List of Pending Bookings
    System-->>Admin: Show Pending Requests
    
    alt Admin Approves Request
        Admin->>System: Click 'Approve'
        System->>DB: Update Status to 'Approved'
        System->>Mail: Trigger Approval Email Notification
        Mail-->>Customer: "Your appointment ID X is approved!"
    else Admin Rejects Request
        Admin->>System: Click 'Reject'
        System->>DB: Update Status to 'Rejected'
        System->>Mail: Trigger Rejection Email Notification
        Mail-->>Customer: "Your appointment ID X is rejected."
    end
    
    %% Therapist Work Lifecycle (Assuming Admin Approved)
    Therapist->>System: Login & View Therapist Dashboard
    System->>DB: Fetch Assigned (Approved) Bookings for Therapist
    DB-->>System: Return Bookings
    System-->>Therapist: Display Work Schedule
    
    %% Following physical service completion
    Therapist->>System: Click 'Mark Work as Done'
    System->>DB: Update Status to 'Completed'
    DB-->>System: Update Success
    System-->>Therapist: Shows "Work marked as done successfully."

    %% Asynchronous Cancellation flow (Can happen anytime before completion)
    opt Cancellation Action
        Customer->>System: Click 'Cancel Booking'
        System->>DB: Retrieve Booking Timestamp
        System->>System: Calculate Time Remaining
        alt Time remaining > 30 mins
            System->>Customer: Process Full 100% Refund
        else Time remaining < 30 mins
            System->>Customer: Process Partial 75% Refund (25% Penalty)
        end
        System->>DB: Update Booking Status to 'Cancelled'
        DB-->>System: Row Updated
        System-->>Customer: Cancellation Complete
    end
